WEBVTT

00:08.550 --> 00:11.552
Susan? I mean, Kara?

00:11.554 --> 00:13.186
Seems like you're leading us
somewhere.

00:13.188 --> 00:15.489
We're taking a ship
to Founders Island,

00:15.491 --> 00:18.425
because judging by the state
of these facilities,

00:18.427 --> 00:21.528
Hub Island has been abandoned
for over a decade.

00:21.530 --> 00:24.031
Dang, I missed big words.

00:24.033 --> 00:27.167
This island is where I trained
to be a Seeker.

00:30.371 --> 00:34.007
So, wait, why are we going
to Founders Island?

00:34.009 --> 00:36.109
I'm taking you back
to your mom.

00:36.111 --> 00:38.045
BMO, would you talk
to this console?

00:38.047 --> 00:40.447
I can't access it
without my implant.

00:40.449 --> 00:42.950
Um...you knew my <i>mom?</i>

00:42.952 --> 00:44.618
You're gonna just drop that?!

00:44.620 --> 00:46.620
Her name is Minerva.

00:46.622 --> 00:47.955
She's a Helper.

00:47.957 --> 00:49.890
[ Ding ]
Oh, thanks, BMO.

00:49.892 --> 00:52.659
Now let's try
and start this sucker.

00:54.128 --> 00:55.562
[ Horn honks ]

00:55.564 --> 00:58.365
What's happening?
Are we being arrested?

00:58.367 --> 01:01.134
Don't worry, ladies. I'll get
you to your senior swim class.

01:01.136 --> 01:03.770
Women: Thank you, Dr. Minnie.

01:03.772 --> 01:05.606
Oh!
Whoa!

01:05.974 --> 01:07.374
[ Gasps ]

01:07.376 --> 01:08.909
[ Tires screech ]

01:10.713 --> 01:13.313
[ Muffled voice ] Hey,
it's not a crosswalk, ya know!

01:13.315 --> 01:16.350
It's -- it's not a...
[ Groans ]

01:26.494 --> 01:27.728
Man: <i>The end.</i>

01:27.730 --> 01:31.164
<i>You have been listening</i>
<i>to "Wizards Way."</i>

01:35.770 --> 01:40.674
So I hear you guys wanna do
some explorin'?

01:40.676 --> 01:42.009
Canteens. Cool.

01:42.011 --> 01:44.478
So what do got for me?

01:44.480 --> 01:47.014
Credits?
I don't take credits.

01:47.016 --> 01:48.815
I want gadgets.

01:48.817 --> 01:52.419
See this gum?
It used to be a book on tape.

01:52.421 --> 01:54.521
Gadgets.

01:54.523 --> 01:55.956
Hmm.

01:55.958 --> 01:58.525
[ Whirring ]

01:58.527 --> 02:00.627
[ Gasps, coughs ]

02:00.629 --> 02:02.996
Hey, not bad.

02:02.998 --> 02:05.198
I'll take it.

02:05.200 --> 02:06.600
Get down to Basket Beach,

02:06.602 --> 02:09.770
and I'll meet you at the boat
in 30 minutes.

02:13.775 --> 02:15.509
[ Beep ]
Hey there.

02:15.511 --> 02:19.046
Uh, you got a couple Hiders
headed for Basket Beach.

02:19.048 --> 02:20.747
You're welcome. Bye.

02:23.551 --> 02:24.885
Yah!

02:24.887 --> 02:26.553
You startled me.
[ Laughs ]

02:26.555 --> 02:29.556
We understand that you can
get us past the Seekers.

02:29.558 --> 02:32.659
Yeah, but you just missed
today's boat.

02:32.661 --> 02:35.729
We understand
that you like gadgets?

02:35.731 --> 02:37.798
I do like them.

02:39.901 --> 02:41.234
[ Click ]

02:41.236 --> 02:45.038
Automated voice:
<i>Hello. Hello. Hello.</i>

02:45.040 --> 02:47.541
I don't like it...
I love it!

02:47.543 --> 02:50.911
Tell ya what, get yourself down
to Basket Beach, ASAP.

02:50.913 --> 02:52.746
You're not coming with us?

02:52.748 --> 02:55.348
Once I determine
you haven't been followed,

02:55.350 --> 02:57.851
I will join you at the boat.

02:57.853 --> 03:00.754
We insist you join us now.

03:03.157 --> 03:05.392
Let's go to the beach.

03:05.394 --> 03:07.594
Dr. Gross: <i>Bring back</i>
<i>those Hiders, y'all!</i>

03:07.596 --> 03:10.664
[ Alarm blaring ]

03:10.666 --> 03:13.433
Aah!

03:13.435 --> 03:17.337
What do you got for me,
Kara?

03:17.339 --> 03:20.073
A sad ol' Hider
with two busted legs.

03:20.075 --> 03:22.743
Oh, I love busted legs!

03:22.745 --> 03:24.077
[ Groans ]

03:24.079 --> 03:25.946
When will he be
at full health?

03:25.948 --> 03:27.447
Tomorrow morning.

03:27.449 --> 03:29.616
Okay, I'll have a transport
here in the morning

03:29.618 --> 03:33.286
to shuttle him to re-ed.

03:33.288 --> 03:35.522
Re-education.

03:39.961 --> 03:41.528
Oh, you're awake.

03:41.530 --> 03:43.597
We set both your legs.
They were broken.

03:43.599 --> 03:46.600
Other than that, you only have
psychological problems.

03:46.602 --> 03:48.602
Well, I could've
told you that.

03:48.604 --> 03:51.271
You don't look like a Hider.
I'm not.

03:51.273 --> 03:54.875
It was a wrong place,
wrong time type of deal.

03:54.877 --> 03:58.812
It's true!
I love it here!

03:58.814 --> 04:00.313
So...white hat.

04:00.315 --> 04:02.382
You're a Helper, huh?
Yes.

04:02.384 --> 04:06.286
I think that fella's
still alive.

04:07.321 --> 04:10.757
<i>Hello. Hello. Hello...</i>

04:10.759 --> 04:12.092
Very funny.

04:12.094 --> 04:14.594
If I don't see you before
tomorrow, enjoy re-education.

04:14.596 --> 04:17.497
You're leavin'?
I have things to do.

04:17.499 --> 04:19.499
What am I gonna look at
when you leave?

04:19.501 --> 04:23.170
Leave some flowers
or somethin'!

04:26.307 --> 04:27.674
These are in the trash?

04:27.676 --> 04:30.710
I think someone died.
Oh, that's great!

04:34.348 --> 04:36.850
You're trying to escape?

04:36.852 --> 04:38.251
No! I'm --

04:38.253 --> 04:40.120
Wrong place, wrong time?

04:40.122 --> 04:42.189
No, no. I have to, uh...

04:42.191 --> 04:43.824
[ Crunch ]
Aah!

04:43.826 --> 04:45.025
Aah!

04:45.027 --> 04:46.526
[ Clank ]
Uhh!

04:46.528 --> 04:48.995
Aah!

04:48.997 --> 04:50.497
This is kind of a setback.

04:50.499 --> 04:53.166
But nothing
a good night's sleep can't fix.

04:53.168 --> 04:57.304
You're not sleeping tonight.
You've got a serious concussion.

04:57.306 --> 04:58.605
And I'm not sleeping tonight...
[ Click ]

04:58.607 --> 05:01.174
because apparently you need
a babysitter.

05:01.176 --> 05:04.144
I'm not a baby.
Okay.

05:04.146 --> 05:05.712
Aah!

05:05.714 --> 05:07.714
Keep those elevated.

05:07.716 --> 05:11.351
I have to figure out a new
lineup for the JV curling team.

05:11.886 --> 05:13.720
You wanna sign my cast?

05:13.722 --> 05:15.055
Which one?

05:15.057 --> 05:17.557
[ Chuckles ]
You're all right, Doc.

05:17.559 --> 05:20.627
Hey, you know I'm not going
to re-ed tomorrow, right?

05:20.629 --> 05:21.795
Oh, yeah?

05:21.797 --> 05:23.730
I'll tell 'em this was
just a misunderstanding,

05:23.732 --> 05:27.334
and then I'll glide out
the front door a free man.

05:27.336 --> 05:30.737
Free to have dinner...
with you?

05:30.739 --> 05:32.172
If you wanted to...

05:32.174 --> 05:34.808
I mean, I-I want to.

05:38.646 --> 05:41.248
So what are you,
a con artist or something?

05:41.250 --> 05:43.516
Yeah, you make it sound
so glamorous.

05:43.518 --> 05:46.519
How about me?
How would you con me?

05:46.521 --> 05:49.723
I wouldn't con <i>you.</i>
<i>I wanna have dinner with you.</i>

05:49.725 --> 05:50.924
[ Laughs ]

05:50.926 --> 05:54.527
Okay, but if you had to,
how would you do it?

05:54.529 --> 05:57.430
Um, okay, You like
helping people, right?

05:57.432 --> 06:00.200
So I'd get you
to feel sorry for me.

06:00.202 --> 06:02.235
I'd act real pitiful.

06:02.237 --> 06:03.770
I don't think
that would work.

06:03.772 --> 06:06.339
I mean you're number one
at number two after all.

06:06.341 --> 06:09.042
[ Laughing ]
[ Laughs ]
You saw my underwear!

06:09.044 --> 06:11.278
You're... [ Laughs ]
Oh!

06:11.280 --> 06:13.413
You're all right, Doc.

06:14.782 --> 06:16.716
[ Pounding on door ]

06:16.718 --> 06:18.084
Open up!

06:18.086 --> 06:19.986
Sure thing. Just a...

06:21.289 --> 06:22.956
Gimme a boost, Doc!

06:22.958 --> 06:24.257
[ Metal door clanks ]

06:24.259 --> 06:26.059
Oh, uh, hello, Dr. Campbell.

06:26.061 --> 06:29.195
Prepare for re-education,
Mertens!

06:29.197 --> 06:30.797
You got
the wrong man, fella.

06:30.799 --> 06:33.800
I've been helping beefcakes like
you catch Hiders for months.

06:33.802 --> 06:35.535
We know you've been playing
both sides.

06:35.537 --> 06:37.270
You think that's not hurtful?

06:37.272 --> 06:39.973
Uh-oh. That was kind of
my only plan.

06:39.975 --> 06:41.942
[ Sobbing ]

06:41.944 --> 06:45.278
Ya finally ran out of quarters,
didn't ya, Marty?

06:45.280 --> 06:48.481
Poor little Marty!

06:48.483 --> 06:51.084
[ Continues sobbing ]

06:51.086 --> 06:53.153
Hold up, guys!

06:53.155 --> 06:54.654
Hey, I'm so sorry
about this,

06:54.656 --> 06:56.990
but I was completing
checkout forms for Mr. Mertens,

06:56.992 --> 06:59.960
and it turns out
he's medically unfit for re-ed.

06:59.962 --> 07:02.495
He's got a rare condition
called garbage body.

07:02.497 --> 07:04.664
Uh, that sounds completely fake

07:04.666 --> 07:06.900
coming from anybody but you,
Dr. Campbell!

07:06.902 --> 07:08.301
[ Laughs ]

07:08.303 --> 07:09.669
See you at the Fun Run!

07:09.671 --> 07:12.505
That was breathtaking
con work, Doc.

07:12.507 --> 07:15.241
So you gonna buy me dinner
or what?

07:15.243 --> 07:17.344
I heard that you loved me

07:17.346 --> 07:19.846
But only for two weeks

07:19.848 --> 07:22.349
To be hopeless or not to be

07:22.351 --> 07:24.417
I'm weak with indecision

07:24.419 --> 07:26.353
Could we begin again

07:26.355 --> 07:29.022
On a terrible date

07:29.024 --> 07:34.527
It would be
greatly appreciated by me

07:34.529 --> 07:38.765
I'll wear my normal shoes
this time

07:38.767 --> 07:41.634
Then maybe you'd like me

07:41.636 --> 07:44.004
Better in the sunlight

07:44.006 --> 07:46.206
If I built a raft

07:46.208 --> 07:48.641
Will you stay with me then

07:48.643 --> 07:53.146
And fall in love
all over again?

07:53.148 --> 07:55.215
Oh, I'm so late!

07:55.217 --> 07:57.550
[ Cooing ]

07:57.552 --> 07:59.552
I'll be home by 7:00.
Mwah!

07:59.554 --> 08:01.354
Hey, can you run a load
of laundry?

08:01.356 --> 08:02.655
You got it.

08:02.657 --> 08:04.290
Should I order us
something for --

08:04.292 --> 08:06.159
Veggie thali
and a mango lassi!

08:06.161 --> 08:07.861
[ Tires peal ]

08:07.863 --> 08:09.362
[ Crickets chirp ]

08:09.364 --> 08:12.298
[ Laughs ]
Yeah, that's Mr. Bear.

08:12.300 --> 08:13.733
Pretty interesting guy,
huh?

08:13.735 --> 08:16.736
Where the heck is
Mommy's Indian food, huh?

08:16.738 --> 08:18.905
[ Laughs ]
Hey, look what you got.

08:18.907 --> 08:21.908
That's one of my old gadgets --
the breadstick wand.

08:21.910 --> 08:23.676
[ Crying ]
[ Running footsteps ]

08:23.678 --> 08:26.413
That must be the grub.
[ Growls ]

08:26.415 --> 08:28.515
End of the line, Mertens!

08:28.517 --> 08:30.417
We're here for vengeance!

08:30.419 --> 08:31.918
[ Chirps ]
Ha!

08:31.920 --> 08:33.820
<i> Hot breadsticks is</i>
<i>what we bake </i>

08:33.822 --> 08:36.423
<i> We don't bake pie</i>
<i>and we don't bake cake </i>

08:36.425 --> 08:39.559
<i> Breadsticks bustling</i>
<i>down the line </i>
<i>You pathetic man.</i>

08:39.860 --> 08:41.394
Uhh!

08:43.097 --> 08:47.167
Don't worry. Daddy's got a raft
stashed around here somewhere.

08:47.169 --> 08:48.768
[ Door opens ]
Hey, guys!

08:48.770 --> 08:51.838
[ Light switch clicks ]
I'm ready for that thali...

08:51.840 --> 08:53.106
Martin?

08:53.108 --> 08:54.374
Finn!

08:54.376 --> 08:56.376
[ Growls ]

08:56.378 --> 08:59.179
Mertens!

08:59.181 --> 09:01.281
Phew!

09:01.283 --> 09:02.916
Let's give Mom a text.

09:02.918 --> 09:06.286
Yeah, I guess we'll just circle
around the island and see if --

09:06.288 --> 09:08.922
[ Thunderclap ]

09:08.924 --> 09:10.924
[ Wailing ]
Freaking Back to Nature Island!

09:10.926 --> 09:14.127
Let's -- let's just wait out
the storm, and then...

09:14.129 --> 09:16.463
Aah! The Guardian!

09:16.465 --> 09:18.832
No, I'm not trying to leave!

09:19.967 --> 09:22.135
[ Wails ]
Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh, shh.

09:22.137 --> 09:24.838
Don't worry.
Daddy's always got a plan.

09:26.107 --> 09:27.407
[ Lights clank ]

09:27.409 --> 09:30.710
Finn, I'll be back for you.
<i>[ Ding ]</i>

09:36.485 --> 09:38.885
Here comes the rascal!

09:38.887 --> 09:40.420
Oop! Wait, wait. Wait! Uh-oh.

09:40.422 --> 09:42.422
Aah!

09:42.424 --> 09:44.324
[ Thud ]
Uhh!

09:44.326 --> 09:46.626
[ Glass shatters ]

09:46.628 --> 09:49.429
[ Beeping ]
<i>Hello. Hello.</i>

09:49.431 --> 09:51.731
<i>Hello.</i>

09:58.506 --> 10:00.006
<i></i>

10:00.008 --> 10:02.342
<i> Hot breadsticks is what</i>
<i>we bake </i>

10:02.344 --> 10:04.978
<i> We don't bake pie</i>
<i>and we don't bake cake </i>

10:04.980 --> 10:07.780
I can't bElieve that of all
the hundreds that have tried,

10:07.782 --> 10:10.416
the gallbag that finally
makes it past the Guardian

10:10.418 --> 10:14.087
is Martin Mertens!

10:16.490 --> 10:18.558
[ Voice breaks ]
I don't understand.

10:24.298 --> 10:28.134
[ Whirring ]

10:28.136 --> 10:30.036
[ Thud ]
Aaayyy!

10:30.038 --> 10:33.173
[ Whirring ]

10:35.309 --> 10:36.543
Hey.

10:36.545 --> 10:37.977
Oh. Hey, what's up?

10:37.979 --> 10:41.114
Nothing. I just haven't said
anything in a while.
